1
00:00:00,434 --> 00:00:08,534
<i>Yeah, turn your sadness into kindness,</i>
<i>your uniqueness into strength</i>

2
00:00:08,709 --> 00:00:16,946
<i>Even if you get lost, let's start walking</i>

3
00:00:17,184 --> 00:00:19,175
<i>One more time</i>

4
00:00:22,189 --> 00:00:25,955
<i>Are you really happy</i>

5
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:29,393
<i>when you're always meeting</i>
<i>to someone's expectations?</i>

6
00:00:29,597 --> 00:00:33,158
<i>Even if you change to</i>
<i>who you really wanna be</i>

7
00:00:33,534 --> 00:00:36,901
<i>Will you always have a great smile?</i>

8
00:00:36,971 --> 00:00:44,400
<i>Dreaming of only "the beginning,"</i>
<i>I wake up</i>

9
00:00:44,478 --> 00:00:53,614
<i>and someday, I'll live on my own.</i>

10
00:00:53,687 --> 00:01:01,719
<i>Yes, precious things are never in shape</i>

11
00:01:01,962 --> 00:01:08,800
<i>You never know what it is</i>
<i>when you get it or lose it</i>

12
00:01:08,869 --> 00:01:16,935
<i>Yeah, turn your sadness into kindness,</i>
<i>your uniqueness into strength</i>

13
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:25,709
<i>Even if you get lost,</i>
<i>let's start walking</i>

14
00:01:25,786 --> 00:01:27,811
<i>One more time</i>

15
00:01:33,538 --> 00:01:34,800
Naruto!

16
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,702
He came in totally late.

17
00:01:41,980 --> 00:01:44,881
Hmm? Where's Sasuke?

18
00:01:45,116 --> 00:01:47,448
The Dosu guy I'm supposed
to fight isn't here, either.

19
00:01:47,819 --> 00:01:49,514
Hey, you guys over there.

20
00:01:49,854 --> 00:01:54,985
Throw out your chests and
show your faces to the spectators!

21
00:02:13,344 --> 00:02:17,246
You guys are the stars
of this "final round"!

22
00:02:20,051 --> 00:02:22,815
Sasuke hasn't been found yet?

23
00:02:23,555 --> 00:02:26,524
A team of several Anbu members
are searching all over,

24
00:02:26,591 --> 00:02:27,956
but they have found nothing.

25
00:02:29,394 --> 00:02:32,454
He might already be in
the hands of Orochimaru...

26
00:02:33,331 --> 00:02:36,494
If that's the case,
we may never find him.

27
00:02:39,904 --> 00:02:41,337
I understand.

28
00:02:44,742 --> 00:02:48,678
Well well... Lord Kazekage.

29
00:03:04,429 --> 00:03:07,489
You must be tired having
come all this way.

30
00:03:07,866 --> 00:03:11,165
No... I'm glad the arena
is in the Leaf Village.

31
00:03:12,103 --> 00:03:16,597
Even though you're still young, it would
probably be a tough journey for you

32
00:03:16,674 --> 00:03:19,404
if you had to go to the trouble
of traveling someplace else.

33
00:03:20,778 --> 00:03:23,906
Shouldn't you decide on
the Fifth Hokage soon?

34
00:03:29,721 --> 00:03:33,157
Please don't treat me
like an old person.

35
00:03:33,625 --> 00:03:36,719
I'm still planning on
being Hokage for another five years...

36
00:03:44,769 --> 00:03:49,069
Now then, I guess it's
about time to begin.

37
00:03:53,778 --> 00:03:59,774
Everyone, thank you very much
for coming

38
00:03:59,851 --> 00:04:04,618
to the Village Hidden in Leaves
Chunin Exam.

39
00:04:05,190 --> 00:04:08,523
We will now begin the
"final round" matches

40
00:04:08,593 --> 00:04:12,324
for the eight who made it
through the preliminaries!

41
00:04:12,664 --> 00:04:15,895
Please watch until the end!

42
00:04:17,502 --> 00:04:22,201
If there are supposed to be eight,
it looks like there's one missing.

43
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:31,644
I have something to tell
you before the match.

44
00:04:34,319 --> 00:04:35,445
Look at this.

45
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:36,479
Huh?!

46
00:04:40,692 --> 00:04:43,525
There was a slight change
to the tournament.

47
00:04:44,329 --> 00:04:48,026
Check who you'll be facing
one more time.

48
00:04:48,967 --> 00:04:52,801
<i>Here, I had more preliminary</i>
<i>matches than the others...</i>

49
00:04:53,905 --> 00:04:56,533
<i>So the Dosu guy dropped out?</i>

50
00:05:01,346 --> 00:05:04,804
<i>I thought I'd pound you here...</i>

51
00:05:05,617 --> 00:05:09,075
<i>If I did that,</i>
<i>there'd be the possibility for me,</i>

52
00:05:09,153 --> 00:05:12,953
<i>as the one remaining after</i>
<i>the first battle, to fight Sasuke.</i>

53
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:18,929
<i>W-What are you?!</i>

54
00:05:26,337 --> 00:05:27,269
Say...

55
00:05:27,672 --> 00:05:28,502
...say.

56
00:05:29,540 --> 00:05:30,199
What?

57
00:05:30,441 --> 00:05:33,467
Umm... Sasuke still hasn't come.

58
00:05:33,911 --> 00:05:34,900
What'll happen?

59
00:05:39,651 --> 00:05:43,280
<i>I wonder if Sasuke really did sneak out</i>
<i>of the hospital room at that time.</i>

60
00:05:48,793 --> 00:05:51,318
Something could've happened to him...

61
00:05:52,463 --> 00:05:56,559
In case a competitor does not arrive
by the start time of his match...

62
00:05:58,569 --> 00:06:00,400
he or she will lose by default!

63
00:06:03,141 --> 00:06:04,699
<i>It doesn't make sense.</i>

64
00:06:05,009 --> 00:06:08,968
<i>Knowing his character,</i>
<i>he'd come even if he had to drag himself.</i>

65
00:06:18,489 --> 00:06:20,787
<i>Where are you going, Gaara?</i>

66
00:06:22,126 --> 00:06:24,686
<i>To verify my existence...</i>
<i>one more time.</i>

67
00:06:42,580 --> 00:06:43,842
<i>One more time.</i>

68
00:06:44,382 --> 00:06:47,283
<i>What's wrong?</i>
<i>You should still be able to move, right?!</i>

69
00:06:52,056 --> 00:06:53,546
<i>Sasuke! Come on!</i>

70
00:07:05,236 --> 00:07:06,498
<i>Could it be...?</i>

71
00:07:06,571 --> 00:07:09,267
<i>Even after I warned him to avoid</i>
<i>doing anything to stand out...</i>

72
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:14,535
<i>He didn't kill that Sasuke Uchiha</i>
<i>also, did he...?</i>

73
00:07:17,548 --> 00:07:19,140
Listen up, you guys.

74
00:07:19,817 --> 00:07:23,253
The terrain is different,
but the rule is that there are no rules,

75
00:07:23,321 --> 00:07:24,652
the same as
in the preliminaries.

76
00:07:25,656 --> 00:07:29,990
The matches will continue until one
or the other dies, or acknowledges defeat.

77
00:07:33,030 --> 00:07:38,127
However, if I judge that it has been settled,
I'll stop the match there.

78
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:40,328
Arguments will not be allowed.

79
00:07:41,406 --> 00:07:42,430
Understood?

80
00:07:45,276 --> 00:07:47,403
So the first match is...

81
00:07:48,312 --> 00:07:50,246
Naruto Uzumaki.

82
00:07:52,417 --> 00:07:53,748
Neji Hyuga

83
00:07:54,519 --> 00:07:58,250
Just those two remain and
the rest of you go to the waiting room.

84
00:08:04,061 --> 00:08:10,261
<i>Byakugan vs. Shadow Clone!</i>

85
00:08:16,774 --> 00:08:19,368
Hey, Hinata! These seats are open.

86
00:08:23,147 --> 00:08:23,909
Uh huh.

87
00:08:25,049 --> 00:08:26,983
This match will be quite interesting

88
00:08:29,987 --> 00:08:31,420
<i>Naruto...</i>

89
00:08:32,423 --> 00:08:33,822
Say, Sakura.

90
00:08:35,693 --> 00:08:38,662
I understand that you're worried
about Sasuke.

91
00:08:38,796 --> 00:08:41,924
But why don't you cheer
for Naruto at least a little bit?

92
00:08:43,334 --> 00:08:46,735
Hmm. You're right.

93
00:08:46,938 --> 00:08:48,200
That being said,

94
00:08:48,272 --> 00:08:51,139
with Neji as his opponent,
Naruto has no chance of winning

95
00:08:51,809 --> 00:08:52,935
That is...!

96
00:08:53,010 --> 00:08:54,409
Not so, is what you're
going to say?

97
00:08:59,217 --> 00:09:02,380
But to think that brat would
survive until this point...

98
00:09:03,855 --> 00:09:06,119
I wonder if this is
as far as it goes

99
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:08,055
for those who survived
just by luck, after all.

100
00:09:08,125 --> 00:09:09,786
That Naruto.

101
00:09:11,195 --> 00:09:13,254
This is not a good opponent at all.

102
00:09:13,564 --> 00:09:16,761
No matter how you look at it,
he can't beat the Hyuga clan.

103
00:09:20,338 --> 00:09:23,671
<i>Well, that's what I thought</i>
<i>at the beginning...</i>

104
00:09:23,875 --> 00:09:27,971
<i>But you'll all be surprised</i>
<i>if you underestimate him.</i>

105
00:09:30,314 --> 00:09:32,111
Akamaru, what's wrong?

106
00:09:34,318 --> 00:09:35,307
What did you say?!

107
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:39,979
What?! Where?!

108
00:09:45,129 --> 00:09:46,061
<i>There!</i>

109
00:09:49,734 --> 00:09:51,964
<i>What's Anbu, the Black Ops,</i>
<i>doing here?</i>

110
00:09:52,904 --> 00:09:54,565
<i>Is something going on...?</i>

111
00:10:04,181 --> 00:10:06,547
You seem like you want
to say something

112
00:10:18,963 --> 00:10:20,794
I said it before, too, didn't I?

113
00:10:22,366 --> 00:10:27,065
<i>A failure is a failure.</i>
<i>You can't change.</i>

114
00:10:30,608 --> 00:10:32,405
<i>I promise...</i>

115
00:10:42,787 --> 00:10:44,254
I'll win, no matter what!

116
00:10:50,261 --> 00:10:52,286
<i>He has the look...</i>
<i>of being sure of himself...</i>

117
00:10:53,030 --> 00:10:55,055
<i>It's as if he's not all worked up...</i>

118
00:10:58,102 --> 00:10:59,967
That makes it
more worthwhile for me.

119
00:11:00,404 --> 00:11:03,669
I look forward to your look
of disappointment...

120
00:11:03,741 --> 00:11:08,508
when you know the true reality...

121
00:11:08,946 --> 00:11:10,811
Stop whining.

122
00:11:15,353 --> 00:11:19,255
Let's... get started!

123
00:11:24,695 --> 00:11:27,061
Now then, round one.

124
00:11:27,898 --> 00:11:28,728
Begin!

125
00:12:31,730 --> 00:12:33,698
Watch carefully, Hanabi.

126
00:12:34,032 --> 00:12:38,731
Nobody has inherited such
a strong Hyuga Kekkei Genkai.

127
00:12:39,404 --> 00:12:41,872
To say nothing of your older sister.

128
00:12:42,941 --> 00:12:44,340
More than big sister?

129
00:12:44,710 --> 00:12:47,076
Perhaps more than you, too.

130
00:12:51,650 --> 00:12:54,744
<i>This time, it's not an opponent</i>
<i>that can be managed easily.</i>

131
00:12:55,153 --> 00:12:57,417
<i>He has that Byakugan.</i>

132
00:13:06,998 --> 00:13:09,057
<i>Close combat is no good...</i>

133
00:13:10,035 --> 00:13:12,936
<i>Does Naruto know that?</i>

134
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:51,173
Idiot! Why would anyone
attack from the front?!

135
00:14:12,697 --> 00:14:14,062
No! Naruto.

136
00:14:56,741 --> 00:14:58,868
The opponent can see
your Chakra Points!

137
00:15:01,513 --> 00:15:03,037
<i>They're called Chakra Points.</i>

138
00:15:03,415 --> 00:15:05,383
<i>If those pressure points</i>
<i>are pressed accurately...</i>

139
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:08,246
<i>the flow of an opponent's Chakra</i>
<i>can be stopped,</i>

140
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:13,485
<i>amplified or controlled at will.</i>

141
00:15:15,694 --> 00:15:17,252
<i>Uh oh!</i>

142
00:15:26,538 --> 00:15:27,903
<i>I missed, huh...?</i>

143
00:15:30,308 --> 00:15:33,300
<i>In other words, he'll press</i>
<i>the pressure point if I get too close</i>

144
00:15:33,378 --> 00:15:34,868
<i>and I'll become unable</i>
<i>to use Jutsu.</i>

145
00:15:35,180 --> 00:15:38,343
<i>That means all I can do</i>
<i>is fight from a distance.</i>

146
00:15:39,584 --> 00:15:43,645
You understand, right?
You have no way of winning.

147
00:15:45,123 --> 00:15:49,389
Heh... All I did was to verify your power.

148
00:15:59,337 --> 00:16:02,738
The real fight is just getting started!

149
00:16:08,013 --> 00:16:09,503
Shadow Clone Jutsu!

150
00:16:13,818 --> 00:16:15,615
<i>You used your head,</i>
<i>didn't you, Naruto?!</i>

151
00:16:15,887 --> 00:16:17,411
<i>With the Shadow Clone Jutsu...</i>

152
00:16:18,089 --> 00:16:20,353
Heh. He's an interesting kid.

153
00:16:21,226 --> 00:16:24,059
Shadow Clone Jutsu is
a Jonin level technique.

154
00:16:24,863 --> 00:16:27,423
To think he could use
such a Jutsu...

155
00:16:28,066 --> 00:16:30,728
Who knows how this'll turn out?

156
00:16:35,907 --> 00:16:37,204
<i>Shadow Clone Jutsu?!</i>

157
00:16:38,143 --> 00:16:43,012
<i>I get it. If Chakra is evenly distributed</i>
<i>among the clones,</i>

158
00:16:43,081 --> 00:16:47,484
<i>indeed, I can't detect the</i>
<i>real one even with my Byakugan.</i>

159
00:16:48,787 --> 00:16:52,223
But there's only one real one,
after all!

160
00:16:53,224 --> 00:16:55,715
Heh. Don't be acting tough!

161
00:16:56,928 --> 00:16:58,657
If you're going to come,
then come.

162
00:17:02,968 --> 00:17:03,900
It's pointless.

163
00:17:04,669 --> 00:17:09,868
In front of that Neji's defense,
it's not just all attacking.

164
00:17:12,610 --> 00:17:13,770
Hey!

165
00:17:14,679 --> 00:17:18,342
Don't... you... underestimate...

166
00:17:18,416 --> 00:17:19,576
...me!

167
00:17:21,753 --> 00:17:23,015
<i>Here they come!</i>

168
00:17:38,636 --> 00:17:39,625
He hit!

169
00:17:43,742 --> 00:17:44,902
Fool.

170
00:17:50,181 --> 00:17:50,909
Wha?!

171
00:17:53,518 --> 00:17:54,746
Dang it!

172
00:17:54,819 --> 00:17:56,184
I'll get you next time!

173
00:18:01,326 --> 00:18:02,156
Here!

174
00:18:13,471 --> 00:18:14,733
This guy...

175
00:18:40,498 --> 00:18:44,832
Does he have eyes behind him?

176
00:18:55,780 --> 00:18:57,577
You're going to become...
the Hokage...?

177
00:18:59,818 --> 00:19:01,752
With this level, it's impossible.

178
00:19:04,856 --> 00:19:08,883
I can generally tell
with these eyes...

179
00:19:09,828 --> 00:19:12,228
Intrinsic abilities are set.

180
00:19:13,498 --> 00:19:18,060
Figuratively speaking,
everything inherent about people is set.

181
00:19:22,173 --> 00:19:23,367
Why...?

182
00:19:25,677 --> 00:19:30,546
Why are you always so
judgmental like that?

183
00:19:30,715 --> 00:19:34,549
Then... are you going to say
that anybody can become the Hokage...

184
00:19:34,619 --> 00:19:35,984
if they just work hard?

185
00:19:38,923 --> 00:19:43,087
Only a very small percentage of
Shinobi are chosen to be the Hokage!

186
00:19:43,828 --> 00:19:45,523
Look more at reality!

187
00:19:46,798 --> 00:19:50,290
Those who become the Hokage
are born with a destiny.

188
00:19:51,202 --> 00:19:53,670
It's not something you become
by trying to become it.

189
00:19:54,239 --> 00:19:56,537
It's determined by destiny.

190
00:19:58,076 --> 00:20:01,307
People must live within
their different respective currents

191
00:20:01,379 --> 00:20:03,279
that can't be defied.

192
00:20:06,384 --> 00:20:13,222
The one single...
destiny everyone has equally...

193
00:20:22,267 --> 00:20:23,427
...is death.

194
00:20:30,909 --> 00:20:32,001
<i>Those eyes...</i>

195
00:20:32,343 --> 00:20:35,176
<i>He still holds a grudge</i>
<i>against the head family, huh?</i>

196
00:20:40,051 --> 00:20:41,143
So...

197
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,449
So what?!

198
00:20:52,096 --> 00:20:57,534
I don't know when to give up!
Shadow Clone Jutsu!

199
00:21:12,251 --> 00:21:15,618
<i>One! First, Tyson jumps and slamdunks</i>

200
00:21:15,688 --> 00:21:19,021
<i>Two! He kisses and hugs everyone</i>
<i>randomly and says "I LOVE YOU"</i>

201
00:21:19,091 --> 00:21:22,527
<i>Three! Masala masters Yoga</i>
<i>but hates curry</i>

202
00:21:22,595 --> 00:21:25,826
<i>Four! Sanchez is a lousy bullfighter. Ole!</i>

203
00:21:25,898 --> 00:21:32,269
<i>All over the world, the sky's smiling,</i>
<i>so look up and smile too</i>

204
00:21:32,338 --> 00:21:39,574
<i>Oh yeah! Oh yeah! Oh yeah!</i>
<i>Fight! Fight! Fight!</i>

205
00:21:49,955 --> 00:21:53,391
<i>One! Bodimahattaya san devotes</i>
<i>his time for digging black ships</i>

206
00:21:53,459 --> 00:21:56,758
<i>Two! Peking Duck, Action Scene,</i>
<i>Chen Lee speeds around on his bike</i>

207
00:21:56,829 --> 00:22:00,128
<i>Three! Popo loves to polish his Coteka</i>

208
00:22:00,199 --> 00:22:03,464
<i>Four! Japanese people,</i>
<i>now lend me you hand!</i>

209
00:22:03,669 --> 00:22:09,699
<i>All over the world, the sky's smiling,</i>
<i>so look up and smile too</i>

210
00:22:09,775 --> 00:22:17,113
<i>Oh yeah! Oh yeah! Oh yeah!</i>
<i>Fight! Fight! Fight!</i>

211
00:22:17,216 --> 00:22:23,644
<i>All over the world, the sky's smiling,</i>
<i>so look up and smile too</i>

212
00:22:23,722 --> 00:22:30,890
<i>Oh yeah! Oh yeah! Oh yeah!</i>
<i>Fight! Fight! Fight!</i>

213
00:22:37,670 --> 00:22:40,935
Darn it! What is going on?!

214
00:22:41,007 --> 00:22:44,875
It was clear that my punch got him,
but I'm the one who was thrown!

215
00:22:45,011 --> 00:22:48,174
Darn it!
Even though I promised Hinata...

216
00:22:48,381 --> 00:22:50,906
I really cannot lose at
a place like this!

217
00:22:51,084 --> 00:22:53,678
The next hit will be the big one
that I'm gonna give him!

218
00:22:53,753 --> 00:22:55,084
Just prepare for it!

219
00:22:55,555 --> 00:22:59,047
Next time, "Ultimate Defense:
Zero Blind Spot!"

220
00:22:59,359 --> 00:23:02,021
I hardly give up things!
